title: City's multi-billion dollar budget, backyard cottages & more on Council Edition
description: What changes will the Seattle City Council make to Mayor Jenny Durkan's proposed $5.9 billion budget? What new investments are city leaders considering in response to Seattle's homelessness crisis? How will major land use decisions related to backyard cottages and surplus land affect affordable housing in your neighborhood? Councilmembers M. Lorena Gonzalez , Lisa Herbold, and Teresa Mosqueda discuss these topics and answer questions from viewers on Council Edition.
